# Bun Package Manager

This project uses **Bun**. Lockfile: `bun.lock`.

## Commands

| Instead of         | Use                |
| ------------------ | ------------------ |
| `npm install`      | `bun install`      |
| `npm add <pkg>`    | `bun add <pkg>`    |
| `npm add -d <pkg>` | `bun add -d <pkg>` |
| `npm remove <pkg>` | `bun remove <pkg>` |
| `npm run <script>` | `bun run <script>` |
| `npx <cmd>`        | `bunx <cmd>`       |

## Agent behavior

- Run package and script commands with `bun` / `bunx`, not `npm`, `pnpm`, or `yarn`.
- Prefer `bun run test`, `bun run dev`, `bun run lint` over `npm test`, etc.
- When adding dependencies, update `package.json` via `bun add` so `bun.lock` stays in sync.
- Do not create or commit `package-lock.json`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`, or `yarn.lock`.

## Examples

```bash
# Install deps
bun install

# Add a dependency
bun add zod

# Run a script
bun run test

# One-off CLI (replaces npx)
bunx shadcn@latest add button
```
